deck: Chief of the NIA, he promoted the American powerhouse project.
description: Malcolm LeStrange is the typical poitical in charge of a shady goverment office: unethical deals with criminal, authorizing illegal experiments in humans and stolen public funds from the national budget for his own interests. As he saw how his own career was at risk, he authorized the project of the American Powerhouse to create a superhero to be sell to the public and make it a product of mass comsumption.
name: Malcolm LeStrange

deck: The American Powerhouse, Allen Powell is a coward paranoid superhuman more interested in the benefits of being a hero than the job itself.
description: A coward and paranoid agent from the NIA who was the only sucessful test subject from the american powerhous project, Allen Powell was choosen to became a superhero to the people of the USA. But the personal traits of Powell, sucha as his paranoias and inefficient were too much obvious, so he was partnered with expert agent Michael Gorsky, so he could make the missions and Powell, as A-Pex, receive the credit and the benefits, of pose like a hero.
name: A-Pex

deck: A veteran and expert black ops agent, Michael Gorsky is the real power behind the A-Pex facade.
description:
An excellent and profesional agent from the NIA, Michael Gorsky was the second option for the project American Powerhouse. Resentful, he still accepted to train the chosen Allen Powell with his powers, depiste hating him.

When it was evident the inefficiency of Powell as superhero, Avis Cattlet cohersed the masoquist Gorsky into make the missions of Powell and fake his hero image. So meanwhile Gorsky make all the dirty work, Powell pose as the hero and take all the glory.
name: Michael Gorsky

deck: Second in comand of the N.I.A. and ex-wife of Michael Gorsky.
description: The manipulative Avis Cutlett cheated her ex-husband, Michael Gorsky, to make the dirty job of A-Pex and make him look as a efficient superhero.
name: Avis Cutlett

deck: Criminal, millionaire, rap singer. Jean-Paul M'butu biggest dream is left behind his criminal past and become a Hollywood mogul.
description: Jean-Paul M'butu is a rap singer with a past as narcotraficant, exthosionist, killer and more, with enough contacts in the criminal and goverment world, included Malcolm LeStrange. His next objetive is become a producer in Hollywood, using people as pop singer Belladonna and Empty.V journalist Vanessa Chang to reach that objetive and clean his money through his movies. However the efforts of A-Pex and Michael Gorsky had spoiled his plans. So he demanded to LeStrange to kill both men.

deck: Religious fanatic who believes herself the reincarnation of Jesuschrist.
description:
Mrs. StMcMiracle was the widow of a tele-evangelist who was sent to prision and who commit suicide there. The Sister StMcMiracle had started a bussiness in internet promising the communion with god trought the net, with a great success. She also won the super-lottery promoted by LeStrange to win the aproval of the public in the powerhouse project. The powers however would be temporary because the unstable nature of them.

Injected with nanobots, StMcMiracle won powers of superstrengh, invulnerability, flight and speed. But when she had to returnt to the NIA office to be deactivated she tricked A-Pex and choose to keep them. She had convinced drs. Cox and Newmar to join her chuch, who give her part of A-Pex own nanobots to keep stable her own powers. Revealed as a religious fanatic on a personal vendetta, StMcMiracle, wanted to bring apocalypse to earth to fullfill the apocalypsis omens.

She was stopped by Michael Gorsky, who know how to deactivate her nanobots.
name: Really Big Jesus

deck: The leader of the Empirikul who aims to eradicate all magic throughout the realms.
description:
Origins

The Imperator's parents, Hieronymus and Abbadona Hellgore, were citizens of a society which worshipped Shuma-Gorath and the magical powers he provided in exchange for human sacrifices. Lord and Lady Hellgore, however, worshipped science as their religion instead, and when they refused to sacrifice their newborn son to their society's god, they were pronounced heretics. In order to save their son, they enclosed him in a balloon-like ship and sent him off into space before being killed at the hands of their government for their crimes against magic.

The child spent his entire childhood in this ship, learning the ways of science and learning to hate magic and its users. Once grown, he declared himself The Imperator, making it his mission to purge the universe of the evil which killed his parents. He set upon a journey to destroy every last magic user and artifact of magical power in existence.

Powers and Abilities

The Imperator has somehow used science to give himself laser vision. It glows green and can be used either as a concussive blast or to start green glowing fires.

He also has built an army which forms the rest of the Empirikul. This includes the robotic Eyebots, which served his parents before him and carry electric pitchforks which also serve as personal teleport devices, and Witchfinder Wolves, who share their master's laser vision.
